- The integer arrays `nums1` and `nums2` must not be null.
- The length of the integer arrays `nums1` and `nums2` must be equal.
- The integer parameter `diff` must be within the range of -10000 to 10000.
- The integer result is the number of pairs `(i, j)` that satisfy the condition `nums1[i] - nums1[j] <= nums2[i] - nums2[j] + diff`.
- The integer result is greater than or equal to 0.